description: Try our easy to follow Seafood Tagine recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
name: Seafood Tagine Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 200g large green king prawns, peeled, deveined, tails intact
800g white fish fillets, cut into chunks
1 tbs ground cumin (plus 2 tsp ground cumin extra)
2 tsp smoked paprika (plus 2 tsp smoked paprika extra)
1 lemon, rind finely grated (plus 1/4 cup lemon juice)
2 tbs olive oil (plus 2 tbs olive oil)
4 garlic cloves, sliced (plus 2 garlic cloves sliced)
couscous, prepared according to packet directions (to serve)

recipeInstructions.text: Place oil, garlic, cumin, paprika, 1/4 cup of lemon juice and salt into a small food processor. Add 3/4 of the coriander, reserving remainder. Process until finely chopped. Transfer half the spice paste to a bowl, add fish, squid and prawns. Set aside to marinate for about 15 minutes while you prepare the sauce.

Meanwhile, heat oil in a frying pan over medium heat and add onions and garlic. Cook for 5 minutes until softened. Add extra cumin and paprika and cook for 2 minutes. Stir in tomato, stock, lemon rind, and reserved spice paste. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes until thick.
Add seafood pieces with any marinade, pushing them into the sauce. Cover and cook for about 6 minutes until seafood changes colour. Top with remaining coriander and serve with couscous.
